Class StateObservation<T>

  • java.lang.Object

    T - is used to identify the unit data class.

    public class StateObservation<T>
extends StateSources
    Class creates an instance of an observation, which is used for an unit. The observation sends the state data with timestamp to the ontology server.

    • Method Detail

      • createAndAddObserver

        private void createAndAddObserver(org.openbase.bco.dal.lib.layer.unit.UnitRemote unitRemote)
                           throws org.openbase.jul.exception.CouldNotPerformException
        Method creates and adds the necessary observer for collecting time and system state information. The observer types are: 1 connectionState: Keep the state of the unit remote connection to verify the correctness of the state changes. N providerServices: Keep the state changes of the different provider services, which are set dependent on the unit remote.
        Parameters:
        unitRemote - is the unit remote to identify the provider services and their state changes.
        Throws:
        org.openbase.jul.exception.CouldNotPerformException - is thrown in case the provider services could not be detected.

      • serviceStateChangeProcessing

        private void serviceStateChangeProcessing(T providerServiceData,
                                          rst.domotic.service.ServiceTemplateType.ServiceTemplate.ServiceType serviceType,
                                          java.lang.String serviceTypeName)
        Method uses the providerService data to build the observation individual, which are used to store the state changes in the ontology. Furthermore, the method observes the validity (e.g. valid timestamp) to ensure correct and complete data points in the ontology. In case of validity the triples are send to the ontology server and, if successfully updated, a rsb notification is done. Current parts of an observation triple bundle are: - is_a observation class - unit id - provider service - timestamp - state change (maybe contains multiple different values, because granularity of differentiation based on service state observer)
        Parameters:
        providerServiceData - are the data containing the state change information.
        serviceType - is the type of provider service, which the data belongs to.
        serviceTypeName - is the type of provider service in ontology string form.

      • rsbNotification

        private void rsbNotification(rst.domotic.service.ServiceTemplateType.ServiceTemplate.ServiceType serviceType)
                      throws java.lang.InterruptedException,
                             org.openbase.jul.exception.CouldNotPerformException
        After successfully updating of the state change(s) the method sends finally a rsb notification (to all listening trigger). The notification contains the ontologyChange, which describes the kind of state change.
        Parameters:
        serviceType - is the type of service and part of the ontologyChange.
        Throws:
        java.lang.InterruptedException - is thrown in case the rsb notification failed by interrupting.
        org.openbase.jul.exception.CouldNotPerformException - is thrown in case the rsb notification failed by processing the rsb instance.
